						<div id="incontent_player" class="gpt-ad"></div><h2><span class="mw-headline" id="Levelling_up">Levelling up</span></h2>
						<p>
							The moveset for Pokémon with&nbsp;<a href="/web/20210512072604/https://essentialsdocs.fandom.com/wiki/Forms" title="Forms">multiple forms</a>&nbsp;can be defined separately for each of those forms in the <a href="/web/20210512072604/https://essentialsdocs.fandom.com/wiki/PBS_file" title="PBS file">PBS file</a> "pokemonforms.txt".
						</p>
						<h2><span id="TM/HM"></span><span class="mw-headline" id="TM.2FHM">TM/HM</span></h2>
						<p>
							Move compatibilities need to be defined in the&nbsp;<a href="/web/20210512072604/https://essentialsdocs.fandom.com/wiki/PBS_file" title="PBS file">PBS file</a>&nbsp;"tm.txt".
						</p><p>
							Moves taught by TM or HM will inherit the PP of the move they replace, if that amount is less than the maximum PP of the newly taught move. This is done in the newest GF games to prevent the abuse of HMs and the now infinite TMs.
						</p>
						<h2><span class="mw-headline" id="Move_Tutor">Move Tutor</span></h2>
						<p>
							Move compatibilities need to be defined in the&nbsp;<a href="/web/20210512072604/https://essentialsdocs.fandom.com/wiki/PBS_file" title="PBS file">PBS file</a>&nbsp;"tm.txt".
						</p><p>
							This allows a Pokémon to learn a special move it may not be able to learn any other way. This service is usually provided by an NPC.
						</p>
						<h2><span class="mw-headline" id="Move_Relearner">Move Relearner</span></h2>
						<p>
							This allows a Pokémon to relearn any move in its level-up moveset which could be learnt at a lower level than the Pokémon's current level. This service is usually provided by an NPC.
						</p>
						<h2><span class="mw-headline" id="Move_Deleter">Move Deleter</span></h2>
						<p>
							This allows a Pokémon to forget any move it currently knows (unless it only knows one move). This is typically only useful for forgetting HM moves, which cannot be overwritten by another move. This service is usually provided by an NPC.
						</p>
						<h2><span class="mw-headline" id="Special_methods">Special methods</span></h2>
						<dl><dd><i>Main article: <a href="/web/20210512072604/https://essentialsdocs.fandom.com/wiki/Editing_a_Pok%C3%A9mon" title="Editing a Pokémon">Editing a Pokémon</a></i></dd></dl>
						<p>
							These include methods that silently teach a Pokémon a move, and are usually used to customise a special Pokémon. They can teach any Pokémon any move with no restrictions.
						</p>
